blog.description: I'm Dave (he/him). I'm a fan of Andi Mack, Riverdale, and Girl Meets World, and other shows and movies. Feel free to send me asks!

summary: Do you think it's more likely that 318 was cut or 317 & 318 were made into one?
question: Do you think it's more likely that 318 was cut or 317 & 318 were made into one?
answer:
I lean more to 3x18 being cut in its entirety, if for no other reason than we know at least 21.5 minutes of footage got cut one way or the other yet they took the time to film 3-4 minutes for a completely new Muffy plot. And we now know Disney was willing to write off a good deal of money by cutting an ep yet they paid for this new story line, which was the only new story line added. This suggests that the new Muffy scenes were a plot necessity to replace scenes that were lost and I think the most likely option is that those lost scenes were at the original wedding. 

We know they didn’t cut the Muffy marathon scenes in 3x14, nor did they cut their scenes in 3x21, so that leaves the bowling alley in 3x17 or the wedding in 3x18. Sure you could do the Machel breakup offscreen but could the show afford to lose such soap opera dramatics at this point? And wouldn’t a plot line that has nothing to do with the Mack family and could very likely be pushed into an earlier or later ep be something that the show would want to keep? And if the show was going to salvage at least part of the original wedding they’d have focused first and foremost on re-shooting the actual ceremony and all the key Bexie and Mack family moments yet there’s no evidence they ever did. I find it very hard to believe that if they planned to air or re-shoot any of 3x18 that they wouldn’t have kept the Muffy scenes since it’s very unlikely Ham played any role in them. 

Fwiw Josh answered an ask on February 20th and he mentioned an upcoming episode filmed on a farm with them in suits so he at least thought the wedding would still air but that was a week before he flew out to join the re-shoots and as he was wrapping up re-shoots he posted that things might not make sense based on the previous production schedule but would make sense when we saw it which would definitely fit with the original wedding being cut. It would also be cleaner to just cut all of 3x18, if they didn’t then that means we’ll have an ep that’s mostly whatever was in 3x17 or moved in from other eps, before cutting to some scenes at the Farm to close out the ep which is a marked departure from how they’ve done big event eps like 2x02 and 2x13 and 3x02 and 3x11 which mostly take place in or around the location of the big event. It looks like 3x14 is pretty much the same as it would have been in otl and the finale is unchanged so that really only leaves 5 eps where story lines can be shuffled around

body:
50 days of Andi Mack

Season 1 Episode 8: Terms of Embarrassment

  • “Future you’s going to be riding in future me’s helicopter” Finally some self confidence from Cyrus
  • I completely forgot Bowie played Ultimate
  • “Milkshake is the new ketchup”
  • Buffy and Cyrus freaking out about how “girly” they are😂

  • Jonah really walked in on andi eating cheetos while binge watching videos of him. The second hand embarrassment is real
  • Cyrus’ guy nod omg
  • “Don’t touch your hair” “But my forehead is lonely!”
  • “You know it Jo… Jolamajama”
  • Jonah just said he loves when Cyrus comes to the games!
  • CYRUS 2.BRO
  • That video Bowie made really gave me feels

summary: Is the character Andi Mack half Asian or a quarter Asian
question: Is the character Andi Mack half Asian or a quarter Asian
answer:
First of all, I think that when it comes to people who are multiracial, reducing them to fractions can actually sometimes be harmful and inaccurate so it’s not something I particularly like to dig into for other people. 

But to answer your question, to our knowledge she would be one quarter Chinese, and Bex would be one half Chinese. We obviously don’t know the accuracy of that because we don’t know the characters’ entire heritage line but based on the 6 or 7 people that we do know in Andi’s family, that would be the most accurate conclusion we could come to.
